olive oil
1 carrot
1 courgette
1 bag chives
½ tin Pineapple Slices
1 cucumber
1 packet pork loin steaks
10 g butter
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Garlic Dip
1 sachet Creole spice blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and courgette into fries.
• Place veggie fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
Spread out evenly, then bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice chives. Reserve some
pineapple juice (2 tbs for 2 people / 1/4 cup for 4
people), then drain pineapple slices
(see ingredients). Roughly chop cucumber.
• In a medium bowl, combine Creole spice blend,
a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil. Add
pork loin steaks and turn to coat.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook
pineapple until lightly browned, 2-3 minutes
each side.
• Transfer to a plate, then roughly chop.

• When the veggie fries have 10 minutes
remaining, return the frying pan to
medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook pork until cooked through,
3-4 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the butter and
reserved pineapple juice, turning pork to coat.
• Transfer to a plate to rest for 5 minutes.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this
adds to the flavour!

• While the pork is cooking, add charred
pineapple, cucumber, shredded cabbage mix,
a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil and
a pinch of salt and pepper to a second medium
bowl. Toss to combine.

• Slice juicy Cajun pork.
• Divide pork, veggie fries and charred pineapple
slaw between plates. Spoon over any remaining
sauce from the pan.
• Garnish with chives. Serve with garlic dip. Enjoy!